The paper focuses on real-time autonomous robot navigation, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The framework also involves human-like interaction and task planning, which suggests the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The use of 3D visual semantic SLAM and RGB-D camera indicates the involvement of computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the framework aims to address the challenges of navigating in a global dynamic environment, which suggests the use of control systems (cs.SY).
